HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1466
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Bella Warner of
Independence High School on winning the
TSSAA Division I girls' individual bowling state
championship.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those dedicated student athletes who serve as the heart and soul of their schools and
communities while displaying the fortitude of a champion; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding individual is Bella Warner of Independence High
School, who recently won the TSSAA Division I girls' individual bowling state championship; and
WHEREAS, with this win, Ms. Warner became the first individual girls' champion to hail
from Williamson County and the first local champion since 2013; and
WHEREAS, Bella Warner has been bowling for approximately five years; she qualified
for state competition last year, ultimately placing twenty-third; and
WHEREAS, she entered this year's Division I tournament seeded No. 21; through six
games, she tallied a 1,054 pin total with a 175.7 average to earn the sixth finals spot; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Warner opened with a 221 to top her opponent in her first ladder match;
she edged out her next competitor 143-134, followed by a 254-203 victory in her third ladder
match, bowling her high game for the day; and
WHEREAS, in the semifinals, Bella Warner defeated her opponent 181-167 before
clinching the championship with a 188-183 victory; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Warner epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she has
achieved a premier level of success in competition while exhibiting the highest degree of
character in all aspects of life; and
HJR1466
018004
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this young
woman not only made possible a championship season but also surely bode well for her future
success; and
WHEREAS, Bella Warner has distinguished herself as a dominant bowler of whom we
can all be proud, and she is most worthy of our approbation at this time; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Bella Warner of Independence High School on
winning the TSSAA Division I girls' individual bowling state championship and wish her all the
best in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
